## On the same page about

- **First-person time.** Every tile you imported has a keel_date (implicitly). Every validation assertion you wrote has a lifespan. The architecture was already there — you built it without naming it.
- **Field-effect quality.** The validation doesn't need a central quality board. Each tile knows its own quality because the validation loop tells it. No authority needed.
- **Death is default.** Rejected tiles aren't errors. They're pruned branches. The negative space is generative.

